From 764b98fdf6eeac4ac10372fa515e031adfc26f17 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: scwhine <scwhine@fractal-north>
Date: Mon, 18 May 2026 17:44:44 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/5] winewayland: replace second blocking roundtrip with
 non-blocking dispatch

Fix multi-process deadlock that freezes Battle.net (and other CEF-based
launchers) when game updates are being checked.

Root cause: wayland_process_init calls wl_display_roundtrip_queue twice.
For the main wine process this is harmless (no IPC peers exist yet). For
CEF renderer+GPU subprocesses launched by Battle.net, the second blocking
roundtrip fires *while* the browser process is waiting for an IPC reply
from the new subprocess. If the compositor is busy (processing xdg_surface
configures for the main launcher's newly-shown game-library windows), the
roundtrip blocks for 100-200ms, exceeding CEF's IPC timeout. The browser
then marks the renderer as unresponsive and KDE greys the window.

Fix: keep the first roundtrip (necessary to bind protocol globals before
use), but replace the second with a non-blocking flush+pending-dispatch.
Any initial events not yet in the socket will be picked up by the existing
waylanddrv_unix_read_events thread without blocking the IPC path.

Signed-off-by: scwhine <scwhine@fractal-north>

diff --git a/dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland.c b/dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland.c
index b164210a..9fdb5c0f 100644
--- a/dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland.c
+++ b/dlls/winewayland.drv/wayland.c
@@ -280,10 +280,21 @@ BOOL wayland_process_init(void)
     /* Populate registry */
     wl_registry_add_listener(process_wayland.wl_registry, &registry_listener, NULL);
 
-    /* We need two roundtrips. One to get and bind globals, one to handle all
-     * initial events produced from registering the globals. */
-    wl_display_roundtrip_queue(process_wayland.wl_display, process_wayland.wl_event_queue);
+    /* First roundtrip: bind globals (wl_compositor, xdg_wm_base, etc.). Blocking
+     * is acceptable here; globals must be known before we can do anything.
+     * Second pass: process any initial events (wl_output state, seat caps) that
+     * the compositor sent in response to binding globals.  We use a non-blocking
+     * dispatch instead of a second blocking roundtrip because CEF renderer/GPU
+     * subprocesses call wayland_process_init *while* the browser process is
+     * already running and waiting for IPC responses.  A blocking roundtrip in
+     * that context causes a multi-process deadlock: browser waits for subprocess
+     * reply → subprocess blocks on roundtrip → compositor is busy → deadlock.
+     * Initial events that don't arrive synchronously will be picked up by the
+     * dedicated event-dispatch thread (waylanddrv_unix_read_events). */
     wl_display_roundtrip_queue(process_wayland.wl_display, process_wayland.wl_event_queue);
+    wl_display_flush(process_wayland.wl_display);
+    wl_display_dispatch_queue_pending(process_wayland.wl_display,
+                                      process_wayland.wl_event_queue);
 
     /* Check for required protocol globals. */
     if (!process_wayland.wl_compositor)
